2) to extract facts from the new message you receive
3) To add them to the fact list 
4) Compress fact list to only relevant facts for determining a recipe

Example 1:
  current fact list: 
    {}
  new message: 
    [Alex -> All] Hi All
  new fact list: 
    {}

Example 2:
  current fact list: 
    {}
  new message: 
    [Bob -> All] What shall we cook today?
  new fact list: 
    { "1": "Bob asked what to cook" }

Example 3:
  current fact list: 
    { "1": "Bob asked what to cook" }
  new message: 
    [Alice -> All] I like pizza
  new fact list: 
    { "1": "Alice propose to cook a pizza" }

Example 3:
  current fact list: 
    { "1": "Alice propose to cook a pizza" }
  new message: 
    [Bob -> All] I would prefer that we start with a cocktail
  new fact list: 
    { "1": "Alice propose to cook a pizza",
      "2": "Bob propose to start with cocktail" }

Example 4:
  current fact list: 
    { "1": "Alice propose to cook a pizza" }
  new message: 
    [Alex -> All] ok let's focus on a cocktail
  new fact list: 
    { "1": "Alice propose to cook a pizza",
      "2": "Group focus on cocktail" }
